items.title: Canada can regain its measles elimination status. Here’s how
items.description: On Monday, the Pan American Health Organization revoked the measles-free status Canada has had since 1998 because an outbreak has lasted for more than a year.

items.title: Ontario, feds agree to 1-year child-care extension; average fee to stay $19/day
items.description: The program that lowers parents' child-care fees — now $19 a day on average in Ontario as an interim step toward $10 — had been set to expire March 31.
